; E. Kozloff leg.; muddy sand gravel, rich in organic matter ; USNM-53337 . Specimen mounted for LM.

tp:treatment-sec.p:
The species was recently redescribed by 
Herranz & Leander (2016)
, and the specimens follow this rather accurate description. The only details that should be added regard the intracuticular substructures related to the female papillae on segments 6 to 8, and middorsal spine length. Female papillae are present in ventrolateral positions on segments 6 and 7 (
Fig. 8E
), and they have a short, somewhat rhomboid intracuticular tube leading to the rounded outlet. Female papillae on segment 8 are ventromedial (
Fig. 8E
), and the intracuticular substructures are crescentic with a small protuberance in the curved part of the structure. Middorsal spine of segment 8 extends well onto segment 9, but never reaches posterior margin of segment (
Fig. 8B
). It was furthermore confirmed that laterodorsal glandular cell outlets 
type
2 are present on segment 8 only (
Fig. 8B
).
